    "body": "### Problem\n\n\nTrigger fullscreen of a half height zellij pane wouldn't redraw nvim buffer.\n\nI understand that this might not be a bug of neovim. Please remove/close if it inappropriate.\n\nThanks\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```\nnvim --version\nNVIM v0.11.4\nBuild type: Release\nLuaJIT 2.1.1753364724\nRun \"nvim -V1 -v\" for more info\n```\n\nSteps to reproduces\n\n- Use default terminal (mac) or kitty stable\n- open zellij session, setup panes like below\n- open vim normally on pane right top\n- open `nvim --clean` on pane right bottom\n\nSetup panes inside tab of zellij\n\n  | LEFT PANEL       | RIGHT TOP: vim    |\n  |------------------|-------------------|\n  | (full height)    | RIGHT BOTTOM: nvim|\n\n\nI trigger fullscreen pane have vim, it redraw normally (vim 9.1)\n\nwhile doing the same with the pane that have nvim, the height stuck at half screen size, `redraw` doesn't change it. If i close nvim, and its reopen normally.\n\n\nHere is the clip for visualization (please play it fullscreen)\nhttps://asciinema.org/a/wOBugCgFRBEpmlSAWnpyLGjCe\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nI think it should display normally as vim.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.11.4\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, vim 9.1\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmac 15.5 (24F74)\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.42.2\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nhomebrew",
